top.value: The objective of the financing is to help develop 50MWac contracted solar power generation capacity.

The objective of the project is to contribute to reducing the high rice import and enhance economic growth through improved production, processing, and marketing, and enhancing private sector participation

The objective of the project is to expand access to affordable and improved housing, equipped with associated basic infrastructure as well as social and market facilities, for the rural population in six (6) regions of Uzbekistan.

The objective of the project is to contribute towards satisfying the increasing demand for electricity in the region by supplying an additional 1,348 GWh per annum (946 GWh from Kaleta HEPP (in Guinea) and 402 GWh from Sambangalou Hydro Electric Power Plant or about 12% of their electrical energy needs in 2020.

The objective of the project is to develop balanced fertilizer and integrated soil fertility management recommendations targeted to specific crops, under specific soil and agro-climatic conditions that will sustainably increase yields and nutritional quality and result in increased returns on fertilizer investments.
The objective of the project is to provide a Line of Finance to the Turk EXIM Bank  to finance infrastructure and industrial projects in IDB member countries.

The project aims at improving in sustainable manner sociological, economic and ecologic balances of the project area, and intensifying and nationalizing the development of natural resources.  It includes:
Improvement of agricultural production, Improvement of crop product ion, Development of bottom land and plains, Improvement of livestock production, Village and pastoral water points, Forest management, Preservation of biodiversity, Improvement of road infrastructure, Accompanying measures: Women activities, Training,
Health care, Support to credit system, Project Management, Studies and supervision of works.
The objective of the project is to contribute to the improvement of health and wellbeing of Pakistani children through eradication of Polio.

The objective of the project is to contribute to the enhancement of livestock production for increased revenues and reduced food insecurity in the Sahel region through improved natural resources management, access to markets, and increased control of transboundary livestock diseases.

The project aims at promoting the economic development of the targeted communities in an integrated and global approach, by increasing their income and also maintaining and guaranteeing their food security thereby reducing the level of poverty in the region. Particularly the project includes to (i) contribute to the training of the producers as well as professionals involved in the development of livestock (ii) provide infrastructures for animal health (iii) provide efficient management of pastoral installations and resources (iv) contribute to the dis_enclavement of the region by providing road infrastructures, and (v) improve nutrition and incomes by adding value to products through efficient processing and marketing through construction of infrastructures like veterinary posts, veterinary laboratories, vaccination parks, cattle markets and abattoirs,
pastoral water wells and boreholes, grazing land development, training, artisanal milk processing, feeder roads, small equipment for animal health, office equipment, animal feeds and small implements, small revolving credit, support to the Executing Agencies including regional project supervision, Consultancy services and Audit.
